723091f-a.title: Manhattan: Rutherford Place - 16th Street (East)
723091f-a.text:
Rutherford Place at the N.W. corner of East 16th Street,
showing St. Georges P.E. Church as photographed westward
across the westerly half of Stuyvesant Park. The photo-
granhers vantage point is Second Avenue at 16th Street.
Note the open latticed spires atop the church. These
became weakened by fire anc were removed (prior to 1890).
About 1871

723092f-a.title: Manhattan: Rutherford Place - 16th Street (East)
723092f-a.text:
Rutherford Place, at the N. W. corner of East 16th Street,
ahowing St. Georges P. E. Church. This edifice erected
in 1845, replaced the first church, a chapel of Trinity
at Beekman and Cliff Street's. The latter was erected in
1752 and was known as the ''Swamp Church''. The sharp peek
of the Memorial House (erected in 1885, the gift of J. P.
Morgan, a communicant) appears at the left margin. The
photographer is viewing westward from a point in the west
half of Stuyvesant Park.
May 17, 1892
Gift of Urbrock Collection
